Articles appear daily touting the benefits of masks. But what does the science really say? Here‚Äôs this from the New England Journal of Medicine in its May 21, 2020 edition: ‚ÄúWe know that wearing a mask outside health care facilities offers little, if any, protection from infection. Public health authorities define a significant exposure to Covid-19 as face-to-face contact within 6 feet with a patient with symptomatic Covid-19 that is sustained for at least a few minutes (and some say more than 10 minutes or even 30 minutes).
